Installation
============

Easy, really. B^)

Any feedback on OSes and hardware you're running this script with is
deeply appreciated! Please mail your successes and fails to
"jochen@zum-quadrat.de". Thanks!


Tested platforms
----------------

Development of gsm-ussd was done on Kubuntu 9.10 and Kubuntu 10.04,
but any moderately recent linux distribution is expected to
work. The package generated by "make deb" was successfully tested on
Debian 5, Sidux 2009/4, Kubuntu 9.10 and Kubuntu 10.04. The package
generated by "make rpm" was successfully tested on Fedora Core 12
and SLES 10.


Tested Hardware
---------------

* Huawei E160 (USB ID 12d1:1003, /dev/ttyUSB1), a.k.a.
	  MEDIONmobile (R) web stick S4011
	  Tchibo Internet Stick
  Development of gsm-ussd happens on this type of modem

* Huawei E1550 (USB ID 12d1:1001 /dev/ttyUSB2)
  Thanks to Tomasz from Poland!

* Huawei E165G (USB ID 12d1:1003, /dev/ttyUSB1) 
  Thanks to Tomasz from Poland!

* Huawei E160X (USB ID 12d1:1003, /dev/ttyUSB1), a.k.a.
	    WebSessions USB-Stick K3565 
